The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, held a press briefing on August 24, 2016. He discussed a range of topics including the Turkish operation in Syria, the increase in prices for EpiPen, the attack at the American University in Kabul, the recent missile launch by North Korea, the situation in Syria, and the Clinton Foundation. Earnest emphasized the importance of the US-Turkey relationship, the need for international cooperation in response to natural disasters, and the administration's commitment to transparency and ethics in government.